New Dehli - Global celebrities including film stars, company executives, politicians and sports personalities descended on Mumbai on Saturday for the wedding celebrations of the son of India's wealthiest man and Reliance Industries boss, Mukesh Ambani. Sundar Pichai, the chief executive of Google, former British prime minister Tony Blair, film stars Rajinikanth and Priyanka Chopra and cricketers Sachin Tendulkar and Hardik Pandya were among the guests. Indian stars Shah Rukh Khan and Ranbir Kapoor were seen dancing with the bridegroom Akash Ambani and plenty of Indians shared photos on social media with #AkashAmbani and #AkashShlokaWedding among the top trending hashtags in India.     A post shared by SRK Universe (@srkuniverse) on Mar 9, 2019 at 5:40am PST The bride, Shloka Mehta, is the daughter of Russell Mehta, a wealthy diamond merchant and managing director of family-owned company Rosy Blue. Celebrations began in Mumbai with feasts, singing and dancing, and other pre-wedding rituals, for the wedding between the two 28-year-olds.     #nitaambani A post shared by  Shloka Mehta (@shloka_mehta_official) on Mar 9, 2019 at 1:34am PST     A post shared by Shloka Mehta (@shloka_mehta_official) on Mar 9, 2019 at 1:35am PST Photos on social media showed elaborate floral decorations and celebrities posing on a lawn before the wedding. Mukesh Ambani, his wife Nita and the bridegroom wore various shades of pink. Maroon 5 always performed for the guests.     A post shared by WeddingSutra.com (@weddingsutra) on Mar 10, 2019 at 1:13pm PDT Ambani, whose business empire spans oil and gas, telecoms and retail, is Asia's richest man and the world's 13th most-wealthiest according to Forbes magazine, with his wealth estimated at $50 billion. See more wedding highlights below.     A post shared by CineRiser (@cineriser) on Mar 11, 2019 at 12:10am PDT     A post shared by Ambani Family (@ambanifamily) on Mar 10, 2019 at 11:35pm PDT     A post shared by Shloka Mehta (@shloka_mehta_official) on Mar 9, 2019 at 11:52am PST     A post shared by Shloka Mehta (@shloka_mehta_official) on Mar 9, 2019 at 11:46am PST     A post shared by Shloka Mehta (@shloka_mehta_official) on Mar 9, 2019 at 11:44am PST